  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "Nullptr in paddle.nextafter\u00a0in PaddlePaddle before 2.6.0. This flaw can cause a runtime crash and a denial of service.\n\nReason for inclusion in AVID: CVE-2023-52302 describes a software vulnerability in PaddlePaddle (a deep learning framework) that can cause a runtime crash and denial of service. This affects AI models/pipelines that rely on PaddlePaddle, i.e., AI systems software stacks. It involves a dependency/framework component (not hardware), fitting the general-purpose AI software supply chain scope. The CVE details provide explicit impact and evidence (null pointer dereference, segfault, DoS), satisfying the security/safety criteria."
  },
